Together with {RiziaDLCText.ExiledTogether}, you did your best to get used to a new life in Kyrute, but it proved to be more difficult than expected.

Your noble status did not mean much here, and almost all of your wealth has been seized in Rizia. You couldn't afford to live in the same way you've been living.

Narrator

Over the next years, despite not feeling at home, you got used to the life in Rumburg.\n\nYou had access to almost everything money could afford. You enjoyed special privileges due to your ties to the queen. There was not much to complain about.

1960|Kingdom of Rumburg

Narrator

Over the next years, you found yourself deep inside Rumburgian court politics. While hesitant at first, Beatrice grew to rely on you more and more as you helped her shepherd through important palace businesses.\n\nOne day, she assigned you a critical job to crush the democratic opposition in the city of Glenhill, which became a bastion of the Rumburgian anti-monarchists. She offered you the Duchy if you succeed.\n\nYou...

Over the next months, you found yourself deep inside Rumburgian court politics. While hesitant at first, Beatrice grew to rely on you more and more as you helped her shepherd through important palace businesses.\n\nShe told you about her plans of "the Grand Awakening." The long awaited war with Sordland was about to begin.

1957|Kingdom of Rumburg

Narrator

Over the next months, relationship between Sordland and Rumburg deteriorated drastically and the Rumburgian army was deployed to the southern borders.

Getting used to Pales was more difficult than what you expected. However, here you could afford to live in the same luxury you did.

Narrator

On your last days, you isolated yourself in your mansion. When the Sordish Armed Forces entered the city, they started to unleash their vengeance on the Rummish nobility in the capital.\n\nWhen they finally got to your house, the soldiers couldn't identify who you were. Despite their orders to arrest Livingston's family, they charged you with death.

You wondered if you could ever be allowed back into Rizia again.\n\nThanks to Queen Beatrice's kindness, you were given one of the seven palaces of the Livingstons in Thornborough. \n\nYour mother was already there, waiting for you.
